# Checklist before hand-off

- [ ] Repository root is named **`aap-demo-<meaningful-slug>`** (or you have documented the equivalent layout for your environment)
- [ ] CasC; **`infra.aap_configuration`**; sensible **`group_vars/all/`** split ‚Äî per **`artifact--casc.mdc`**
- [ ] **`aap_config.yml`** / **`aap_cleanup.yml`** follow the standard structure, deletion order, confirmation pattern, and the organization-deletion guard ‚Äî per **`artifact--casc-playbooks.mdc`**
- [ ] **`demo_organization_name`** and **`demo_inventory_name`** are unique across every sibling artifact (checked with the `grep` command in **`artifact--demo-variables.mdc`**), not a shared placeholder
- [ ] **`collections/requirements.yml`** and **`ansible.cfg.example`** with `collections_path` (or equivalent) for **`collections/`**; **README** documents collection install, Ansible config layout, secrets versus **`*.example`** files, and ordered **`playbooks/setup/`** naming when applicable ‚Äî per **`artifact--layout.mdc`**
- [ ] README and **`docs/`** follow **`all--english-content.mdc`**; no emoji, strong structure, cross-links, tables, ASCII diagrams as needed ‚Äî per **`artifact--readme.mdc`**
- [ ] README's first badge is the `Status` badge (`WIP` or `Ready`) ‚Äî per **`artifact--status-badge.mdc`**
- [ ] FQCN, explicit `collections:` on plays, tags, handlers, vault, **`verify.yml`**, **`docs/setup.md`** ‚Äî per **`artifact--ansible-quality.mdc`**
- [ ] **Roles** (if any): init under **`roles/<role-name>/`**; **`tasks/main.yml`** as entry with included task files; documented **`defaults/`**; internal constants in **`vars/`**; **`meta/main.yml`** with dependencies; secrets only via vault ‚Äî per **`artifact--roles.mdc`**
- [ ] **`artifact--code-comments.mdc`** standards applied; playbooks and tasks documented per that rule
- [ ] Every supporting dependency has setup/teardown playbooks, job templates, and a dual-mode flag where applicable ‚Äî per **`artifact--self-sufficiency.mdc`**
- [ ] If the artifact provisions and tears down infrastructure, a `demo_manage_infrastructure` flag gates the CasC infra objects, with mode-aware variable/secret banners (in both `demo_variables.yml.example` and `vault.yml.example`) and assertions ‚Äî per **`artifact--demo-deployment-modes.mdc`**
- [ ] **`docs/testing.md`** exists and its status summary reflects the current tested state ‚Äî per **`artifact--testing-log.mdc`**
- [ ] **`vault.yml.example`** follows the standard naming, structure, and content-split rules ‚Äî per **`artifact--vault-naming.mdc`**
- [ ] **`demo_variables.yml.example`** follows the standard section order and prefix conventions ‚Äî per **`artifact--demo-variables.mdc`**
- [ ] The Git repository configuration block follows the standard shape ‚Äî per **`artifact--git-repository.mdc`**
- [ ] Custom Execution Environment (if in scope) follows the standard build/CasC/credential pattern ‚Äî per **`artifact--execution-environment.mdc`**
- [ ] All **`artifact--*`** and **`all--*`** rule files present in **`.agents/rules/`**
- [ ] Cross-tool rule wiring present ‚Äî per **`artifact--layout.mdc`**'s **Cross-tool rule wiring** section: `.cursor/rules` symlinked to `.agents/rules`, and `opencode.json` at the artifact root.
